@NODE "Mail_26" " Blitz running on Morphos "
From: Anton Reinauer <ants@paradise.net.nz>
Date: 10-30-00 00:38:13
Subject: @{b}Blitz running on Morphos@{ub}

  I've got MorphOS running on the 1200, and Blitz is running fine under
it's 68k emulation, and compiled progs are running fine too. The only
problem I had is with my UDP_Chat- I think it's the `SetInt 5'
instruction, which sounds about right- as I think 68k interupts aren't
supported.  

  Overall Morphos runs well- I think it actually runs 68k progs slower
than the 040/25- but because (I think) the system calls are in native
PPC, it actually runs faster overall (on my 200 mhz 603e). It
definitely is much more responsive to input, and the GUI is faster too
(only AGA here- you would probably see a big improvement with a
BVision). PPC programs are running faster too- about 15-20% faster for
lha/unlzx. 
   I've had some stuff not work- I think due to running wb 3.0- it needs
3.1- I've had similar problems before with WB3.0 , on 3.1 roms (I'll
have to make a 3.1 boot disk :) 

    Seeya- Anton
-- 
   Anton Reinauer <ants@paradise.net.nz>  
  
       http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/ants 


@ENDNODE

