@NODE "Mail_35" " can anyone explain this problem (addition) "
From: Peter Thor <pettho-0@student.luth.se>
Date: 10-26-00 13:42:45
Subject: @{b}can anyone explain this problem (addition)@{ub}

Hey, found my old Motorola programmers ref manual, in it it says:

    Line 1111 Emulator (Unimplemented F-Line Opcode)

So, i maybe your  instruction-cache and data-cache are fooling with
eachother providing the CPU with a faulty opcode due to updating
faultyness, hope that's it, correct me if I'm wrong please.

So, try flushing the Cache, if it doesnt work, well I don't know :)

Note, this can also occour when you write selfmodifying code - evil on
cache-friendly systems :)

//Thor
