> 
> while not end of list
>    x=readitem list 1
>    y=readitem list 2
>    additem list3=x
>    additem list4=y
> wend

I'm not really sure what you are trying to achieve, but...

If your "Input" Lists are the same size you could do something like

RESET_LIST{*LIst1}
RESET_LIST{*LIST2}
While NEXT_ITEM{*List1}
   IF NEXT_ITEM{*List2}
      ADD_ITEM{*LIST3}
      ADD_ITEM{*LIST4}
      ;  Copy contents of current List1 Item
      ;  and List2 Item to current List3 and List4 items
   endif
WEND

You'd need to modify it a bit if your input lists are not the same
size.

Give me a private e-mail and I'll try to explain a bit better.
> 
> There is just no clear description and example on how to do that. I
> can make
> it work with listviews, but I heard there was some bug or so?

There is an example in the DLL readme from Dev/Basic/DLL.lha
I've never tried it, but David McMinn invented it so it should work
:-)

Give me a private mail with what you are trying to achieve and I may
be able to help more.

Cheers

