On 20-Oct-00, Tony Rolfe wrote:

C=Why are you doing this.    Why not simply load up the file to one list
C=and point the Listview at it?

Because I need to use more lists. One list goes to the listview, with only the
names(the file is a playlist file) and another is internal to load the file
into the player. I did that because having full pathnames in the listview can
make the names become not readable as they go out of the listview.

Also I need temp lists of both the names and the full pathnames, at some
point. When someone wants to make a new playlist and while doing that changes
her/his mind and clicks "forget" ;-) Thenthe old list will still be there.

Hm that just gave me an idea. I could do it the other way around. And leave
the player window fully working. That way u have some more internal
multitasking.

As a side note, the amount of safety features I`ve built in is quite
amazing(if I think about it, though I bet it`s comon practice). I have done
the weirdest things with it and the only very rare crash(which only I seem to
have) I can get out of it is the old #080000020 guru in combination with
yam(which might be from a replay routine anyways). To be honest, I`m quite
proud. Might just be no big deal for others, but it`s my first Amiga app.
That`s also why the static lists in blitz bother me. Makes it less foolproof.
Maybe I`m a perfectionist, but I see it as a challenge.

C=Of course I could be completely missing something

As I explained above =)

