> *PlayList  for the List and *PlayItem for the Item.     You then call
> every function using the List name (Except for IntiList - should I
> change that??  Dave set it up that way originally and I've never
> thought to change it.)

No, I think you need to pass the address of the item pointer for initlist 
because the routine allocates memory for the DLL and then stores the 
address of the item pointer in there. So it knows where to store the 
current item pointer after a NEXT_ITEM etc.


