@NODE "Mail_77" " Re: JSR's "
From: David McMinn <dave@satanicdreams.com>
Date: 10-14-00 09:40:31
Subject: @{b}Re: JSR's@{ub}

> Will this 
> a) work

Yeah, I think that should work. I've done that to reference labels 
before, although never JSR to them. SHould work the same, cos the 
function has no idea where the address is.

> b) completely stuff up the stack

If it works, that shouldn`t happen. After all, it's just a jsr/rts (and 
the rts takes care of the stack change made by the jsr), so you're gonna 
end up going back into the function so the stack used by it will be 
cleaned up.


