> > don't know how it will check the local / global variable thing. But if
> > the subroutine is pure asm then there is nothing wrong and it can be
> > safely done.
> 
> You're right about local variables, probably best to preserve that inside 
> the function before you JSR. Global variables should be OK though, since 
> Blitz always uses a5 for them, and that never changes (or it shouldn't :)
> 
> Obviously, you won't be able to use any of the function's local variables 
> either since (as far as the compiler is concerned) the subroutine will 
> not be in the function.

I've just explained (in detail) to Curt what I'm trying to do, so I
won't repeat it here.   Sufficient to say that I'm only using
"external variables" in the JSR'ed routine, so I hope I'll be all
right.    It's gonna be a BIG job to do it and I'll let you all know
how it went (eventually).


