I'm not sure HOW to do it exactly, but here's a (horrible) pointer :)

- you can get the address of your functions (like you get those of variables)
	(i'm not sure blitz can do this, just guessing, only got my total amiga
	 working last night! YAY!)
- put these addresses into an array (scary!) of .l 
- make an empty function

- when you need a function, look up the address in an array,
assign that addres to your empty function (or maybe just a .l variable)
and call it.

As I said, not sure it can be done, but would be nice if it could :)

Ralf


