You mean like trying to hack function pointers (like in C) into Blitz? Nope :)

The closest thing you can do is get the address with the label in front of it 
like you mentioned before and JSR to the address (with the right parameters in 
the right registers).

I suppose you could emulate it with a macro, to hide the ASM, although it would 
be more tricky to get results from the function (without making the macro 
parameters a bit more messy than a normal function).


