@NODE "Mail_99" " More on Blitz source "
From: James L Boyd <james@thesurfaces.net>
Date: 10-10-00 20:12:47
Subject: @{b}More on Blitz source@{ub}

Hi all,

Does anyone have any firm ideas for what they'd like to do with the Blitz
source?

Reading the mail I got from Simon Armstrong, he *doesn't* want to release it
(the source) publicly, but would rather pass it to somebody with the will
and ability to develop it (he's against making it public because "blitz2.s
is not a pretty sight" :)

So, any skilled coders who want to work on Blitz (presumably on a non-profit
basis), if you have some realistic plans for the source, let me know and
I'll pass the info on to Simon! Don't say you'll do something with it if
you're just curious -- you have to be genuinely interested and able to do
something worthwhile with it!

See ya,
