@NODE "Mail_114" " MUI-Stack "
From: Peter Thor <peterthor@engineer.com>
Date: 10-20-00 19:36:58
Subject: @{b}MUI-Stack@{ub}

Hey!

Someone, I can't remember who had a problem with their programs using MUI
crashing.

I haven't tried this out, but it's included in dev/basic/_MUIBB2Lamp.lha_

Here ya go, it's written by Robert Hutchinson.

;--------------------------------------------------------

  ;--- Add summat to the stack to stop MUI spacking :)
  ;    astack.w is the amount of bytes to add to the stack!
  ;
  astack.w = 8096 ; The amount to append to the current stack!
  DEFTYPE .StackSwapStruct stackswap
  DEFTYPE .Task *mytask
  *mytask     = FindTask_(0)
  stacksize.l = *mytask\tc_SPUpper-*mytask\tc_SPLower+astack
  *newstack   = AllocVec_(stacksize.l,0)
  stackswap\stk_Lower   = *newstack
  stackswap\stk_Upper   = *newstack+stacksize
  stackswap\stk_Pointer = stackswap\stk_Upper

  If *newstack
    StackSwap_(&stackswap)
  EndIf

; put rest of your programs code...
...
...
...

;- RUN THIS WHEN PROGRAM FINISHES

  StackSwap_(&stackswap)
  FreeVec_(*newstack)

;----------------------------------------------------

Cheers, Thor
;--
Peter Thor, Amiga Programmer
thor@pagan-games.com
IRC: Joru
ICQ: 11277616

@ENDNODE

