No, not even the window is displayed. Blitz won't compile my MUI programs,
period. It 'hangs' just before the two 1-pixel bars reach the end, and won't
do anything until I press the !PANIC! button. Then it just goes back to the
editor and I can resume coding.

Until I try and compile again. At which point it freezes up, because the
previous 'program' is still in memory. Anyone got any ideas what's causing
this?
 
> I've got MUI.RES, what's  different with the MUI2.RES?

More classes (BetterString.mcc) etc. mainly, but also a StackOpen macro that
allows you to change a program's stack.

Rob Hutchinson can give you more info, he made it.

Cheers,
