@NODE "Mail_150" " Re: Scrolling text "
From: David McMinn <dave@satanicdreams.com>
Date: 10-18-00 23:43:18
Subject: @{b}Re: Scrolling text@{ub}

> > Which way is the best to scroll text in window (horizomtal). It shoul be
> > smooth and of course fast. Thanks for any help.
> 
> I think you'd need to render the text to a superbitmap, but I've no idea how
> to actually *do* it ;)

Depends. I think using a superbitmap would involve scrolling the whole 
window/bitmap. If you want to just scroll a section, you'd probably have 
to do it yourself:
1) create a buffer bitmap
2) update the buffer bitmap
3) use something like BltBitMapRastPort_ to draw it to the window
4) go back to 2

You get a semi-double buffered approach in that you are not actually 
rendering to the display, however since the display isn't updated 
instantaneously (as it could be if you were using a screen, all you need 
to do is change the pointers, in this case it must copy the data from the 
bitmap to the window) it might be a bit jerky.

Windows aren't the best thing for smooth scrolling graphics :)


