@NODE "Mail_163" " Re: The First Stumbling Block "
From: David McMinn <dave@satanicdreams.com>
Date: 10-15-00 10:30:30
Subject: @{b}Re: The First Stumbling Block@{ub}

> I just installed the Ultimate Blitz Basic CD and just ran into my
> first head scratcher. I loaded an example from the CD and hit
> "compile and run." I got an error message that said "libs not found."
> 
> What libs and where is it looking for them?

Does the source code have commands that are "?????". If it does then it 
is the library that those commands are in that it cannot find. Hopefully 
you don't have too many ?????'s.

Did you install BSS from the CD? The installer script on the CD does not 
do this for you, you need to go into the BSS1 (I think) drawer and run 
the install script from there.

Failing that, there are loads of libraries on Aminet, all handily 
collected at http://www.blitz-2000.redhotant.com in the Archives-
>Libraries (Blitz) section. What source file is it and we can try to find 
out what library it is?

Oh, and what is the exact libs not found error? Does it have a number?


